article.description: — Moses Wood posted 18 points as Portland narrowly beat UC Davis 65-60 on Wednesday.
article.headline: Wood scores 18 to lead Portland over UC Davis 65-60
article.linkText: Wood scores 18 to lead Portland over UC Davis 65-60
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- — Moses Wood posted 18 points as Portland narrowly beat UC Davis 65-60 on Wednesday. Tyler Robertson had 13 points for Portland (9-6). Mike Meadows added 12 points and six assists. Ezra Manjon had 20 points and eight rebounds for the Aggies (6-4), whose four-game win streak ended. Caleb Fuller added 17 points. UC Davis totaled 26 points in the second half, a season low for the team. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
